        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/53/67",
        "text": [
          "٥٣. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): السَّخَاءُ مَا كَانَ ابْتِدَاءً، فَأَمَّا مَا كَانَ عَنْ مَسْأَلَةِ فَحَيَاءٌ وَتَذَمُّمٌ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "53. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: Generosity is that which is by one’s own initiative, because giving on being asked is either out of self-respect or to avoid rebuke."
          ]
        }
      }
